id: pm-ps85
title: Fix TOON array-of-objects continuation lines double-indent
description: "renderToonValue prepended an extra '${indent}  ' to each continuation line of array-item objects, doubling indentation. Subsequent line was rendered at depth+1 already; the extra prefix caused 4 spaces where 2 were expected. Saves ~30-50% leading whitespace in list/search outputs."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: agent-ux,output,pm-cli,token-efficiency,toon
created_at: "2026-05-16T21:54:01.343Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-16T23:13:08.419Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: list/search items render as YAML-style aligned blocks; all 1309 tests pass; no test asserted the buggy doubled indent.
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Fixed and guarded by TOON indentation regression.
expected_result: Array-object continuation lines render at the expected indentation without doubled leading spaces.
actual_result: Regression asserts two-space continuation and rejects doubled indent; linked test and release gate passed.
